category.name: movies/film
description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.


https://youtu.be/mazoYfVl9eg

category.name: movies/film
description:
I have a short movie script written (about 3-5 minutes) and I would love to see it through to a short film!

I have taken a summer course in directing and have made a few short videos previously (super amateur with friends and family :) ). My goal is to realize this idea and make this the best it can be, while having fun and learning new skills/meeting people along the way. Therefore, if you want to be part of this project we would need (any level of experience):

-actors <br>-camera person <br>-sound person <br>-editor/post production help

Please message me/join if you're interested!! The goal would be to shoot the final film in July or August in one day (hopefully on a weekend). 

Hope this will work out!!

Simone
name: Luzern Film Makers🎬

category.name: movies/film
description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Du liebst Filme, gehst aber nicht allzu gerne alleine ins Kino und findest gerade keinen, der dich begleitet? Dann bist du richtig hier! Falls du einen bestimmten Film sehen möchtest, so schreib mir doch eine Nachricht und ich poste den Event. Zudem kann man zusätzlich zum Kinobesuch noch was essen oder trinken gehen und auch mal einen Filmabend veranstalten.
Cheers & Bis bald!

It's all about movies! You want to go see a movie, not really keen on going by yourself and there's no one around to join? Well then, this is the right group for you! If there's a specific movie in mind you'd like to watch, just send me a message and I can post the event. Plus - why not combine it with having dinner and drinks together?
See you soon - Cheers!

category.name: movies/film
description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.


https://youtu.be/mazoYfVl9eg
name: Mobile Motion Filmmakers Meetup

category.name: movies/film
description: This is a group for anyone interested in video production. We organize different workshops based on everyone's needs. We supply the necessary equipment and love to share our professional experience with the novices ! We cover every aspect of video production; From filming, lighting and editing all the way to post-production; color grading, special effects, motion graphics and chroma keying ! Why spending tons of money in school when you can meet enthusiasts who love to share with others their secrets and tricks... For those who already own a DSLR or a regular camera but want to learn in depth some of its features, our former B&H sales rep will be more than happy to help out.

description:
We’re two friends from New York/Wallis and a local from Basel who would like to meet people that are interested in watching movies at the kult.kino in Basel. The films at kult.kino are mostly beyond mainstream and simply great and thought-provoking.
We will suggest a movie every two or three weeks (on various days of the week) and are looking forward to extending the evening with a drink and open discussion regarding the film.
Interested? Come along or bring a friend! We are looking forward to meeting you.

Liz & Jenny

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

description:
I have a short movie script written (about 3-5 minutes) and I would love to see it through to a short film!

I have taken a summer course in directing and have made a few short videos previously (super amateur with friends and family :) ). My goal is to realize this idea and make this the best it can be, while having fun and learning new skills/meeting people along the way. Therefore, if you want to be part of this project we would need (any level of experience):

-actors <br>-camera person <br>-sound person <br>-editor/post production help

Please message me/join if you're interested!! The goal would be to shoot the final film in July or August in one day (hopefully on a weekend). 

Hope this will work out!!

Simone

category.name: movies/film
description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.


https://youtu.be/mazoYfVl9eg

description: This is a group for anyone interested in video production. We organize different workshops based on everyone's needs. We supply the necessary equipment and love to share our professional experience with the novices ! We cover every aspect of video production; From filming, lighting and editing all the way to post-production; color grading, special effects, motion graphics and chroma keying ! Why spending tons of money in school when you can meet enthusiasts who love to share with others their secrets and tricks... For those who already own a DSLR or a regular camera but want to learn in depth some of its features, our former B&H sales rep will be more than happy to help out.

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.

category.name: movies/film
description:
This group is a spin-off of the Bern-based Sci-fi/Fantasy Film & Book Club Meetup group (https://www.meetup.com/Sci-Fi-Fantasy-Film-Book-Group/). Over the last one and half year of its existence some of the core members would from time to time arrange viewings of films outside of the Sci-Fi/Fantasy genre. The common thread amongst the films were that they all dealt with social, historical and political themes – hence the title of the group “Films for the Conscious”, as in aware of sociopolitical and economic issues. We felt this trend warranted that we set up a separate group, especially since this would hopefully allow us to meet some of you we otherwise wouldn’t. 

Primarily the group will meet and watch films in organizers’ homes (on their big screens). The films that will be screened will be announced along with any given Meetup event and will not be subject to change. Occasionally we will also watch films in the theatres here in Bern or perhaps even visit a film festival. The aim of the group is to introduce, (re)discover and discuss high quality films which have social commentary as a central or significant theme. The Bern Meetup community is an international one, therefore films not in English will be screened with English subtitles. 

Prior to the start of the film for home cinema evenings we’ll have a potluck dinner where everyone brings something (which will be coordinated to some degree in the comment sections of any particular Meetup event). For theatre outings we will usually meet at a restaurant in close proximity to the cinema for dinner (or drinks). In this case it is also possible to meet us directly at the cinema if you cannot make the pre-event. 

NO SHOW POLICY: Because we have limited space (we mostly meet in our homes), we wait for all our members to show up before starting movies, and because we try to make sure there's enough food for everyone (often food which people spent time preparing), repeated no shows may be banned from the group. Everyone has the occasional emergency, and we are pretty understanding, but we ask you, if at all possible, to cancel at least 24 hours in advance if you can't make it. We look forward to meeting you!
name: Films for the Conscious

description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.


https://youtu.be/mazoYfVl9eg

description: This is a group for anyone interested in video production. We organize different workshops based on everyone's needs. We supply the necessary equipment and love to share our professional experience with the novices ! We cover every aspect of video production; From filming, lighting and editing all the way to post-production; color grading, special effects, motion graphics and chroma keying ! Why spending tons of money in school when you can meet enthusiasts who love to share with others their secrets and tricks... For those who already own a DSLR or a regular camera but want to learn in depth some of its features, our former B&H sales rep will be more than happy to help out.

-actors <br>-camera person <br>-sound person <br>-editor/post production help

Please message me/join if you're interested!! The goal would be to shoot the final film in July or August in one day (hopefully on a weekend). 

Hope this will work out!!

Simone

The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

Please message me/join if you're interested!! The goal would be to shoot the final film in July or August in one day (hopefully on a weekend). 

Hope this will work out!!

Simone

See you soon - Cheers!

Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

category.name: movies/film
description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.
name: Zürich VR/AR Meetup

category.name: movies/film
description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.


https://youtu.be/mazoYfVl9eg

Interested? Come along or bring a friend! We are looking forward to meeting you.

Liz & Jenny

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

category.name: movies/film
description:
This group is a spin-off of the Bern-based Sci-fi/Fantasy Film & Book Club Meetup group (https://www.meetup.com/Sci-Fi-Fantasy-Film-Book-Group/). Over the last one and half year of its existence some of the core members would from time to time arrange viewings of films outside of the Sci-Fi/Fantasy genre. The common thread amongst the films were that they all dealt with social, historical and political themes – hence the title of the group “Films for the Conscious”, as in aware of sociopolitical and economic issues. We felt this trend warranted that we set up a separate group, especially since this would hopefully allow us to meet some of you we otherwise wouldn’t. 

Primarily the group will meet and watch films in organizers’ homes (on their big screens). The films that will be screened will be announced along with any given Meetup event and will not be subject to change. Occasionally we will also watch films in the theatres here in Bern or perhaps even visit a film festival. The aim of the group is to introduce, (re)discover and discuss high quality films which have social commentary as a central or significant theme. The Bern Meetup community is an international one, therefore films not in English will be screened with English subtitles. 

Prior to the start of the film for home cinema evenings we’ll have a potluck dinner where everyone brings something (which will be coordinated to some degree in the comment sections of any particular Meetup event). For theatre outings we will usually meet at a restaurant in close proximity to the cinema for dinner (or drinks). In this case it is also possible to meet us directly at the cinema if you cannot make the pre-event. 

NO SHOW POLICY: Because we have limited space (we mostly meet in our homes), we wait for all our members to show up before starting movies, and because we try to make sure there's enough food for everyone (often food which people spent time preparing), repeated no shows may be banned from the group. Everyone has the occasional emergency, and we are pretty understanding, but we ask you, if at all possible, to cancel at least 24 hours in advance if you can't make it. We look forward to meeting you!

category.name: movies/film
description:
This group is a spin-off of the Bern-based Sci-fi/Fantasy Film & Book Club Meetup group (https://www.meetup.com/Sci-Fi-Fantasy-Film-Book-Group/). Over the last one and half year of its existence some of the core members would from time to time arrange viewings of films outside of the Sci-Fi/Fantasy genre. The common thread amongst the films were that they all dealt with social, historical and political themes – hence the title of the group “Films for the Conscious”, as in aware of sociopolitical and economic issues. We felt this trend warranted that we set up a separate group, especially since this would hopefully allow us to meet some of you we otherwise wouldn’t. 

Primarily the group will meet and watch films in organizers’ homes (on their big screens). The films that will be screened will be announced along with any given Meetup event and will not be subject to change. Occasionally we will also watch films in the theatres here in Bern or perhaps even visit a film festival. The aim of the group is to introduce, (re)discover and discuss high quality films which have social commentary as a central or significant theme. The Bern Meetup community is an international one, therefore films not in English will be screened with English subtitles. 

Prior to the start of the film for home cinema evenings we’ll have a potluck dinner where everyone brings something (which will be coordinated to some degree in the comment sections of any particular Meetup event). For theatre outings we will usually meet at a restaurant in close proximity to the cinema for dinner (or drinks). In this case it is also possible to meet us directly at the cinema if you cannot make the pre-event. 

NO SHOW POLICY: Because we have limited space (we mostly meet in our homes), we wait for all our members to show up before starting movies, and because we try to make sure there's enough food for everyone (often food which people spent time preparing), repeated no shows may be banned from the group. Everyone has the occasional emergency, and we are pretty understanding, but we ask you, if at all possible, to cancel at least 24 hours in advance if you can't make it. We look forward to meeting you!

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.


https://youtu.be/mazoYfVl9eg

I have a short movie script written (about 3-5 minutes) and I would love to see it through to a short film!

I have taken a summer course in directing and have made a few short videos previously (super amateur with friends and family :) ). My goal is to realize this idea and make this the best it can be, while having fun and learning new skills/meeting people along the way. Therefore, if you want to be part of this project we would need (any level of experience):

-actors <br>-camera person <br>-sound person <br>-editor/post production help

Please message me/join if you're interested!! The goal would be to shoot the final film in July or August in one day (hopefully on a weekend). 

Hope this will work out!!

Simone

Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

description:
I have a short movie script written (about 3-5 minutes) and I would love to see it through to a short film!

I have taken a summer course in directing and have made a few short videos previously (super amateur with friends and family :) ). My goal is to realize this idea and make this the best it can be, while having fun and learning new skills/meeting people along the way. Therefore, if you want to be part of this project we would need (any level of experience):

-actors <br>-camera person <br>-sound person <br>-editor/post production help

Please message me/join if you're interested!! The goal would be to shoot the final film in July or August in one day (hopefully on a weekend). 

Hope this will work out!!

Simone

category.name: movies/film
description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

category.name: movies/film
description:
This group is a spin-off of the Bern-based Sci-fi/Fantasy Film & Book Club Meetup group (https://www.meetup.com/Sci-Fi-Fantasy-Film-Book-Group/). Over the last one and half year of its existence some of the core members would from time to time arrange viewings of films outside of the Sci-Fi/Fantasy genre. The common thread amongst the films were that they all dealt with social, historical and political themes – hence the title of the group “Films for the Conscious”, as in aware of sociopolitical and economic issues. We felt this trend warranted that we set up a separate group, especially since this would hopefully allow us to meet some of you we otherwise wouldn’t. 

Primarily the group will meet and watch films in organizers’ homes (on their big screens). The films that will be screened will be announced along with any given Meetup event and will not be subject to change. Occasionally we will also watch films in the theatres here in Bern or perhaps even visit a film festival. The aim of the group is to introduce, (re)discover and discuss high quality films which have social commentary as a central or significant theme. The Bern Meetup community is an international one, therefore films not in English will be screened with English subtitles. 

Prior to the start of the film for home cinema evenings we’ll have a potluck dinner where everyone brings something (which will be coordinated to some degree in the comment sections of any particular Meetup event). For theatre outings we will usually meet at a restaurant in close proximity to the cinema for dinner (or drinks). In this case it is also possible to meet us directly at the cinema if you cannot make the pre-event. 

NO SHOW POLICY: Because we have limited space (we mostly meet in our homes), we wait for all our members to show up before starting movies, and because we try to make sure there's enough food for everyone (often food which people spent time preparing), repeated no shows may be banned from the group. Everyone has the occasional emergency, and we are pretty understanding, but we ask you, if at all possible, to cancel at least 24 hours in advance if you can't make it. We look forward to meeting you!
name: Films for the Conscious

If you have a specific movie in mind or if you wanna organize a Movie Night yourself on a specific day, just send me a mail and I can post the event.

see you soon at the movies!
Cheers, Guillaume

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

Simone

description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.


https://youtu.be/mazoYfVl9eg

description:
Du liebst Filme, gehst aber nicht allzu gerne alleine ins Kino und findest gerade keinen, der dich begleitet? Dann bist du richtig hier! Falls du einen bestimmten Film sehen möchtest, so schreib mir doch eine Nachricht und ich poste den Event. Zudem kann man zusätzlich zum Kinobesuch noch was essen oder trinken gehen und auch mal einen Filmabend veranstalten.
Cheers & Bis bald!

It's all about movies! You want to go see a movie, not really keen on going by yourself and there's no one around to join? Well then, this is the right group for you! If there's a specific movie in mind you'd like to watch, just send me a message and I can post the event. Plus - why not combine it with having dinner and drinks together?
See you soon - Cheers!

Interested? Come along or bring a friend! We are looking forward to meeting you.

Liz & Jenny

description: This is a group for anyone interested in video production. We organize different workshops based on everyone's needs. We supply the necessary equipment and love to share our professional experience with the novices ! We cover every aspect of video production; From filming, lighting and editing all the way to post-production; color grading, special effects, motion graphics and chroma keying ! Why spending tons of money in school when you can meet enthusiasts who love to share with others their secrets and tricks... For those who already own a DSLR or a regular camera but want to learn in depth some of its features, our former B&H sales rep will be more than happy to help out.

category.name: movies/film
description:
This group is a spin-off of the Bern-based Sci-fi/Fantasy Film & Book Club Meetup group (https://www.meetup.com/Sci-Fi-Fantasy-Film-Book-Group/). Over the last one and half year of its existence some of the core members would from time to time arrange viewings of films outside of the Sci-Fi/Fantasy genre. The common thread amongst the films were that they all dealt with social, historical and political themes – hence the title of the group “Films for the Conscious”, as in aware of sociopolitical and economic issues. We felt this trend warranted that we set up a separate group, especially since this would hopefully allow us to meet some of you we otherwise wouldn’t. 

Primarily the group will meet and watch films in organizers’ homes (on their big screens). The films that will be screened will be announced along with any given Meetup event and will not be subject to change. Occasionally we will also watch films in the theatres here in Bern or perhaps even visit a film festival. The aim of the group is to introduce, (re)discover and discuss high quality films which have social commentary as a central or significant theme. The Bern Meetup community is an international one, therefore films not in English will be screened with English subtitles. 

Prior to the start of the film for home cinema evenings we’ll have a potluck dinner where everyone brings something (which will be coordinated to some degree in the comment sections of any particular Meetup event). For theatre outings we will usually meet at a restaurant in close proximity to the cinema for dinner (or drinks). In this case it is also possible to meet us directly at the cinema if you cannot make the pre-event. 

NO SHOW POLICY: Because we have limited space (we mostly meet in our homes), we wait for all our members to show up before starting movies, and because we try to make sure there's enough food for everyone (often food which people spent time preparing), repeated no shows may be banned from the group. Everyone has the occasional emergency, and we are pretty understanding, but we ask you, if at all possible, to cancel at least 24 hours in advance if you can't make it. We look forward to meeting you!
name: Films for the Conscious

description:

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

description:

category.name: movies/film
description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

category.name: movies/film
description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.

description:
Machst du No oder Low-Budget-Filme? Möchtest du Filmemacher und Filmfans in Zürich treffen? Möchtest du ein Team finden, welches dir bei deinem nächsten Projekt hilft, dich als Freiwillige/r melden oder dich einfach über Filmemachen austauschen?

Komm zum monatlichen Filmemacher Meetup von Mobile Motion Film Festival, um dich mit anderen Gleichgesinnten zu vernetzen. Teilt eure Erfahrungen aus und helft euch gegenseitig.

Jeder ist willkommen, keine Erfahrung oder Fähigkeiten erforderlich.

_____________


Are you into making low or no budget films? Do you want to meet filmmakers and film fans in Zurich? Want to find a team to work on your next project, volunteer for some set-time, or just talk about filmmaking? Come to Mobile Motion Film Festival's Monthly Filmmakers Meetup to network with other like minded people. Share experiences and help each other out.

Everyone is welcome, no experience or skills required.


https://youtu.be/mazoYfVl9eg

category.name: movies/film
description:
This group is a spin-off of the Bern-based Sci-fi/Fantasy Film & Book Club Meetup group (https://www.meetup.com/Sci-Fi-Fantasy-Film-Book-Group/). Over the last one and half year of its existence some of the core members would from time to time arrange viewings of films outside of the Sci-Fi/Fantasy genre. The common thread amongst the films were that they all dealt with social, historical and political themes – hence the title of the group “Films for the Conscious”, as in aware of sociopolitical and economic issues. We felt this trend warranted that we set up a separate group, especially since this would hopefully allow us to meet some of you we otherwise wouldn’t. 

Primarily the group will meet and watch films in organizers’ homes (on their big screens). The films that will be screened will be announced along with any given Meetup event and will not be subject to change. Occasionally we will also watch films in the theatres here in Bern or perhaps even visit a film festival. The aim of the group is to introduce, (re)discover and discuss high quality films which have social commentary as a central or significant theme. The Bern Meetup community is an international one, therefore films not in English will be screened with English subtitles. 

Prior to the start of the film for home cinema evenings we’ll have a potluck dinner where everyone brings something (which will be coordinated to some degree in the comment sections of any particular Meetup event). For theatre outings we will usually meet at a restaurant in close proximity to the cinema for dinner (or drinks). In this case it is also possible to meet us directly at the cinema if you cannot make the pre-event. 

NO SHOW POLICY: Because we have limited space (we mostly meet in our homes), we wait for all our members to show up before starting movies, and because we try to make sure there's enough food for everyone (often food which people spent time preparing), repeated no shows may be banned from the group. Everyone has the occasional emergency, and we are pretty understanding, but we ask you, if at all possible, to cancel at least 24 hours in advance if you can't make it. We look forward to meeting you!
name: Films for the Conscious

description:
The place to go typically for those who make content, finance content, appear in content, or offer tools to make content. Bringing together people from universities, companies and independent studios to see what collaborative VR or AR experiences we can create – movies, educational content, games and research projects.

By joining, you're taking the following pledge: 

1) I'll keep any shared ideas safe and if I want to use them, I'll involve their originator. 

2) I'll structure my ventures so as to keep local IP's and local resources' returns local. 

3) I'll come to have fun, not to monitor the competition. I'll catalyze any projects I can. 


Naturally, I'll inform anyone I bring along of the same. 

Say "aye". 

Aye.

description:
I have a short movie script written (about 3-5 minutes) and I would love to see it through to a short film!

I have taken a summer course in directing and have made a few short videos previously (super amateur with friends and family :) ). My goal is to realize this idea and make this the best it can be, while having fun and learning new skills/meeting people along the way. Therefore, if you want to be part of this project we would need (any level of experience):

-actors <br>-camera person <br>-sound person <br>-editor/post production help

Please message me/join if you're interested!! The goal would be to shoot the final film in July or August in one day (hopefully on a weekend). 

Hope this will work out!!

Simone

category.name: movies/film
description:
We meet up after work or on a weekend in or close to Zurich to first quickly plan and then straightaway go shoot some footage. The idea is not to spend hours talking but rather to go out there and get some run-and-gun, no- to low-budget filming done, for practice, fun and content creation, be it documentary or fiction.

We help each other out to realise different projects in different roles. Bring your Arri Alexa or your iPhone, your microphone or your make-up kit or simply turn up with your awesome music, acting or editing skills; whatever it is you want to do in filmmaking this is your chance to actually do it. No experience needed (but lots of experience welcome!), main languages are German and English but any other language welcome too.

description: This is a group for anyone interested in video production. We organize different workshops based on everyone's needs. We supply the necessary equipment and love to share our professional experience with the novices ! We cover every aspect of video production; From filming, lighting and editing all the way to post-production; color grading, special effects, motion graphics and chroma keying ! Why spending tons of money in school when you can meet enthusiasts who love to share with others their secrets and tricks... For those who already own a DSLR or a regular camera but want to learn in depth some of its features, our former B&H sales rep will be more than happy to help out.

category.name: movies/film
description: This is a group for anyone interested in video production. We organize different workshops based on everyone's needs. We supply the necessary equipment and love to share our professional experience with the novices ! We cover every aspect of video production; From filming, lighting and editing all the way to post-production; color grading, special effects, motion graphics and chroma keying ! Why spending tons of money in school when you can meet enthusiasts who love to share with others their secrets and tricks... For those who already own a DSLR or a regular camera but want to learn in depth some of its features, our former B&H sales rep will be more than happy to help out.

description:
Basel Film Club is about Film Making! (Acting, Production, Direction, Music, Script and much more..)
If you are passionate about filmmaking & enjoy the craft, this is the group to be in. Beginners & Experts alike.
An opportunity to be creative, network, exchange ideas, get hands on experience and have fun.
Join us & Let's meet up.

category.name: movies/film
description:
We’re two friends from New York/Wallis and a local from Basel who would like to meet people that are interested in watching movies at the kult.kino in Basel. The films at kult.kino are mostly beyond mainstream and simply great and thought-provoking.
We will suggest a movie every two or three weeks (on various days of the week) and are looking forward to extending the evening with a drink and open discussion regarding the film.
Interested? Come along or bring a friend! We are looking forward to meeting you.

Liz & Jenny
name: Movies @ kult.kino Basel
organizer.name: Jennifer
